-- German Stocks Resume Climb After ECB Allots Funds; DAX Rises 1%
-- B y   P e t e r   L e v r i n g
-- 2012-02-29T10:38:29Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-29/german-stocks-resume-climb-after-ecb-allots-funds-as-commerzbank-advances.html
German stocks resumed gains after
the European Central Bank said it will lend 529.5 billion euro
for 1,092 days to 800 financial institutions.  Economists predicted an allotment of 470 billion euros,
according to the median of 28 estimates in a Bloomberg News
survey. Banks borrowed 489 billion euros in the first three-year
operation in December.  The benchmark stock index, the DAX Index, rose 1 percent at
11:34 a.m. after briefly paring gains. The index of 30 companies
traded on the Frankfurt Stock Exchange rose 65.12 to 6,952.75.
Among the stocks in the index, 27 rose and 3 fell.
Gains in the DAX were led by  BASF SE (BAS) ,  Siemens AG (SIE)  and  Deutsche
Bank AG. (DBK)    To contact the reporter on this story:
